The paper deals with the problem of exploring an unknown region using a team of aerial robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves recursive depth-first search, which is a common technique used in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The problem also involves coordination and communication among the robots, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a solution using algorithms and analysis, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of cameras and image processing for mapping the region, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
